                </div>

                <div style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto;">
                    <div style="background: white; padding: 30px; margin-bottom: 20px; border-left: 4px solid #BCC6CC;">
                        <h3 style="font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #2B332A;">How long does planning permission take in London?</h3>
                        <p style="color: #6B7280; line-height: 1.8;">Most applications are determined within 8 weeks. Some boroughs can be faster (6 weeks) while complex applications may take 13 weeks. We'll give you a realistic timeline based on your specific borough and project type.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div style="background: white; padding: 30px; margin-bottom: 20px; border-left: 4px solid #BCC6CC;">
                        <h3 style="font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #2B332A;">Do I need planning permission for my extension?</h3>
                        <p style="color: #6B7280; line-height: 1.8;">It depends on the size, location, and your property type. Many single-storey rear extensions fall under Permitted Development. However, conservation areas, flats, and Article 4 directions affect this. We offer a free assessment to determine what you need.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div style="background: white; padding: 30px; margin-bottom: 20px; border-left: 4px solid #BCC6CC;">
                        <h3 style="font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #2B332A;">What's included in your service?</h3>
                        <p style="color: #6B7280; line-height: 1.8;">Site survey, all planning drawings (floor plans, elevations, site location plan), planning application form, design & access statement where required, full submission to council, and ongoing liaison until determination. Council fees are additional.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div style="background: white; padding: 30px; margin-bottom: 20px; border-left: 4px solid #BCC6CC;">
                        <h3 style="font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #2B332A;">What if planning permission is refused?</h3>
                        <p style="color: #6B7280; line-height: 1.8;">We have a 92% first-time approval rate. If refused, we offer free advice on amendments and resubmission. We can also handle planning appeals if appropriate. Our goal is to get your project approved.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div style="background: white; padding: 30px; margin-bottom: 20px; border-left: 4px solid #BCC6CC;">
                        <h3 style="font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #2B332A;">Do you handle Building Regulations too?</h3>
                        <p style="color: #6B7280; line-height: 1.8;">Yes, we can provide Building Regulations drawings as an additional service. We work with approved structural engineers and can coordinate the full technical package needed for construction.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

